com/repos/datalad/datalad/milestones/30/labels", "id": 1992953, "node_id": "MDk6TWlsZXN0b25lMTk5Mjk1Mw==", "number": 30, "title": "Homogeneous path resolution", "description": "This was discussed multiple times. Last in #766.\r\n\r\nA simple solution is to resolve any path _before_ trying to resolve a dataset. This exposes whether a dataset was explicitely provided, and consequently whether relative paths should be interpreted relative to it, and not to CWD.\r\n\r\nExample patch:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/mih/datalad/commit/e23e976b093110433accdf5ffd0a263df686e9ff", "creator": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "open_issues": 0, "closed_issues": 9, "state": "closed", "created_at": "2016-09-09T09:30:39Z", "updated_at": "2016-10-20T16:50:09Z", "due_on": "2016-09-30T07:00:00Z", "closed_at": "2016-10-20T16:50:09Z"}, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2016-09-09T11:03:16Z", "updated_at": "2016-09-13T16:07:07Z", "closed_at": "2016-09-13T16:07:07Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "```\nmih@meiner /tmp/some (git)-[master] % datalad ls\n.  [annex]  master  - 2016-09-09/12:46:31  OK\nmih@meiner /tmp/some (git)-[master] % mkdir test\nmih@meiner /tmp/some (git)-[master] % cd test\nmih@meiner /tmp/some/test (git)-[master] % datalad create deep\n2016-09-09 12:59:55,433 [INFO   ] Creating a new annex repo at /tmp/some/test/deep (create.py:217)\nCreated dataset at /tmp/some/test/deep.\n```\n\nSo far all good, treats path as relative to CWD. But:\n\n```\nmih@meiner /tmp/some/test (git)-[master] % datalad create -d /tmp/some notthatdeep\nusage: datalad [-h] [-l {critical,error,warning,info,debug,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9}]\n               [-p {condor}] [--version] [--dbg] [--idbg] [-C PATH]\n               {search-datasets,aggregate-metadata,create,install,add,publish,uninstall,update,create-publication-target-sshwebserver,add-sibling,modify-subdataset-urls,unlock,save,test,crawl,crawl-init,ls,clean,add-archive-content,download-url,create-test-dataset}\n               ...\ndatalad: error: unrecognized arguments: -d notthatdeep\n```\n\nIMHO it should also get `-d` now and also support paths that are relative to a given dataset -- if only for consistency.\n", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/d